The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Welspun-Gujarat Stahl Rohren Ltd?s net profit for the year ended March 31, 2005 has dipped 50 per cent to Rs 38.8 crore from Rs 78.6 crore for the year ended March 31, 2004. The company?s total income has increased by 15.8 per cent to Rs 1,061.4 crore last financial year compared with Rs 915.9 crore in 2003-04, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Monnet Ispat has reported a growth of 337 per cent in net profit at Rs 123.83 crore for the financial year ended March 31, 2005. Executive vice-chairman and managing director Sandeep Jajodia said its board had approved a dividend of 35 per cent, taking the total payout for the fiscal to 60 per cent. The companys turnover jumped by 152 per cent to Rs 777.77 crore in 2004-05 from Rs 309.59 crore in 2003-04.

 KSL and Industries Ltd has posted a net sales of Rs 153.62 crore during the year ended March 31, 2005 against Rs 87.16 crore in the previous year, a rise of 76 per cent. Its net profit increased by 1286 per cent to Rs 10.67 crore compared with Rs 77 lakh during the year ended March 31, 2004. The board has recommended a dividend of Rs 5 per share and bonus shares in the ratio of two units for every one held.

 Stone India Limited has reported a net profit at Rs 2.38 crore during 2004-05 compared with a loss of Rs 8.96 crore during the previous year. The turnover during the year was Rs 46.51 crore compared with Rs 34.45 crore in the previous fiscal, a jump of 35 per cent. 

 Essar Shipping Limited (ESL) has recorded a total income of Rs 232.76 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2005 compared with Rs 247.21 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year. Net profit was Rs 120.12 crore, a growth of 190.63 per cent. Total income for 2004-05 grew by 50.77 per cent to Rs 1112.54 crore compared with Rs 737.89 crore last year. Net profit was Rs 460.58 crore, a growth of 195.66 per cent.

 Chambal Fertilisers amp; Chemicals (CFC) has posted a 49.01 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 186.25 crore for the fiscal ended March 31, 2005 compared with Rs 124.99 crore in 2003-04. Total income for the reporting fiscal increased to Rs 2,631.90 crore from Rs 2,244.72 crore in 2003-04, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 Zensar Technologies, a joint venture of the RPG group and Fujitsu, has reported a consolidated net profit of Rs 39.1 crore for the year ended March 31, 2005 compared with Rs 12.6 crore for the previous year. Zensar?s revenues for 2004-05 showed an increase of 29 per cent at Rs 345 crore compared with Rs 267 crore in the same period last year. The company has announced a dividend of 23 per cent for a share with a face value of Rs 10 each.

